reviews_data.review_text: Wanted to try something new for our family outing so we decided to come here for some patties and coffee. The customer service was  -3/10, the pastries was 5/10 & the coffee was -1/10 considering I asked for iced coffee but they gave me hot in 80 degree weather! Probably won't be back.

Dear Tous Le Jour,
I've been a loyal fan of this coffee shop since moving here. it's truly one of my favorite spots in town. The coffee and pastries are consistently great, the atmosphere is cozy, and the staff are always kind and welcoming.

My friends and I haven’t been going since reading about the low scores and violations in the health inspections. As someone who genuinely loves and supports this place, I hope the team is able to address the issues raised and take the necessary steps to bring everything up to standard.

I'm rooting for you and looking forward to many more great cups of coffee here in the future!

Used to be my go to place.  No more.  Horrific sanitation scores - repeatedly. Either they don’t care or they care incapable of maintaining a safe sanitation level. Not a problem with their other location but I’m really turned off.

That young brunette woman needs to get fired. I’ve had a couple occasions with her being passive aggressive and downright rude, making me feel like I was inconveniencing her by simply placing my order. Her customer service is unacceptable.

I also saw her involved in a verbal altercation with another customer/family outside a couple of months ago. If she cannot conduct herself respectfully and professionally, she should not be in a customer service role.

Everything is 100% perfect!! Food is always fresh and the bakery, usually flaky and fluffy!
I tried most of their bakery and ordered 2 cakes and they were absolutely delicious and not over sugary, just balanced and creamy!

reviews_data.review_text: Unfortunately the owners are disassociated with the standards of cleanliness. They have low marks from the health board, for multiple years. They're neglected to train their employees, give process to the employees about how to keep clean, and store food. They do not spend money on protecting the kitchen from roaches, and in part this is also the responsibility of the overall building management. Yet that only means the retail tenants need to be more aggressive with bug product on the ground where the food should never be... so it is only a matter of time before they change ownership or close. There are other quality French cafes with baked goods in the area.

There’s a lady who’s almost always there and usually makes the drinks. One time, she even took my order. She always looks annoyed, acts like she doesn’t hear you, and just stares blankly when you talk. This has happened many times, and at this point, I really hope she’s not there the next time I go in.

Love this place and it is considered one of my favorites.  I will make it a point to drive there at least once a month since I am 21/2 hours away. Sadly, Tous les Jours doesn't want to make a satellite home here in Chapin SC.  They would definitely knock the socks off any place here.
Rated B two inspections in a row for BUGS,  Dirty dishes and prep areas.
Sanitation grade is 86% gross
B sanitation score... 😬

The food was underwhelming, and most of the trails were empty. The woman at the front desk was extremely rude—no greeting and absolutely no customer service. It took her an unusually long time just to prepare coffee and tea. I’m genuinely surprised that a business would allow someone like this to represent them. Personally, I wouldn’t stop here again.

We live on the coast of North Carolina- Wilmington and don't have many bakeries; my son Will Adams brought us a strawberry cloud cake for my birthday.  We loved it! I make sure he and his wife Clara bring one to our home each time he comes to visit. We're waiting on a peach cloud for his birthday next week. I'm dying to try the green tea cake. Thank you, Susan Adams

Barista at this joint have to improve with speed and thoughtfulness, look at this large Americano with over pour of hot liquid.
This is a take out order with full of hot liquid!!! I’m wasn’t aware how full this was and it just spilled out all over my hand. 🔥🫳🏽 😫and the bag of foods.
Costs of large Americano tasted like hot water not a coffee not worth money spends.
Serving speed was slow even though I’m the one the only one waiting for my order.
There’re some fly flying inside the food cabinet.
I’m the fan of Tours Les Jours, but this time feel regret about giving tip out for this take out items, feeling like wanting my money back.

We had a terrible experience with this bakery on July 2nd between 1-4 pm. Our manager was rude and unapologetic.

We’ve ordered cakes from here many times and have always had a nice experience. However, this time, they made a huge mistake. They gave us a small cake instead of the large cake we ordered, and they charged us for a medium cake instead of the small cake we received.

It’s a 1-hour drive back and forth from our house, and this ruined my daughter’s birthday. The manager refused to admit their mistake and wouldn’t even say their name. We could only reach their extension number, which ended with 0969.

We will definitely never buy from this bakery again.
It’s an overpriced place. Not a big choice of cakes.

The best bakery around. The Tiramisu coffee? Amazing, my favorite Danish is the custard pretzel twist it's delectable. The cakes they make on site can be a little pricey but are worth it if you can swing it.
The food has no favor.  The steak & cheese had no taste if you didn't use the garlic sauce.  Don't let me go off about the meatballs sub. Horrible
It was vert quiet place and had some pastries. I definitely would recommend to try their Mango pastry.

We wanted to visit this place from a long time and finally got a chance to visit last week. The cakes and the bakery items were amazing. Tried the cloud cake and the tiramisu latte and they were amazing. Will be back definitely to try the rest of the items.
immediately run here for the honey lavender matcha latte w oat milk bro u wont regret
Very nice place for croissants and desserts and coffee. Good vibes
Love this bakery.  Everything is delicious 😋

I'm addicted!  These pastries are some of the best.  Nothing is too sweet.  They add fresh fruit in some desserts.  The cloud cakes are perfect.  The cream you see in pictures is a light cream not icing.  Everything is reasonably priced.  And their dough is so light and fluffy in everything I've eaten from there.

I’ll start off with the coffee is amazing! I ordered the 20oz iced caramel macchiato. I love matcha and they had a few different matcha options that I’d love to try in the future. I also ordered the spinach & cheese danish. They serve it warm and it tastes very good but it’s kind of small in comparison to other spinach danishes that I’ve had, and it costs more.

I also ordered a lemon macaron. Pretty large for a macaron! I love the texture but it was too tart. Not a huge fan of the flavor but I’m sure the other macarons are good. And they have a large variety to include pistachio, red velvet, and earl grey.

Parking is very difficult. I drove around multiple times and to even park in their lot is hard because it is so tiny. And I paid $17 for a coffee, danish, and macaron which really should’ve been a few dollars less.
I love it so much. Food was amazing 10/10 experience.

The place is pretty, so are the pastries- (that’s just about all some of them have (looks)), but there are like four good items. The service took a little while but patience is the greatest of all virtues, I guess. I know the workers were trying their best but they 1) seemed uninterested, 2) the coffee tasted like tea- steamed pretty lazily. I NEVER leave reviews, but this was straight up bad and sad. I was so excited to try Tous Les Jours.

The cloud cakes have nothing cloudy about them. Theyre also too expensive for what they are! They’re tough and the flavors a feel nonexistent. They taste like vanilla cakes with food coloring. The icing felt old, it was super greasy. As if the icing had begun to separate between the sugar and butter- or worse; it wasn’t mixed well. $7 for that. The macarons also had little to no flavor apart from sugar. They tasted like fridge. I was a little sad to taste everything, knowing the packaging says “freshly baked everyday”. Nothing about it tasted freshly baked. The mocha just tasted like packaged hot chocolate mix. No strong hints of anything else (coffee). Made my tummy hurt. I don’t mean to sound entitled but I led a bakery program last summer for kids and I can tell you, I know when cakes are old. Everything was sort of tough. The chocolate on stuff also felt very pasty and chalky. The chocolate was waxy, and seemed low quality. Some stuff is good but please don’t try this with high expectations. Not worth a visit imo. Sorry :(

Visiting from out of town morning of 6/6/25- searched for a quaint coffee/pastry shop and chose Tous Les Jours.  Food was well presented and atmosphere just ok - but the Barista was very unfriendly and disinterested and basically seemed annoyed by the customers.  With so many shops like this in the Charlotte area - I’ll search for one with friendlier employees.

I recently visited Tous les Jours located at 4625 Piedmont Row Dr #105, Charlotte, NC 28210,
Here’s my review using my 5-star rating system: cleanliness, service, decor, food, and prices.

Cleanliness: The restaurant was clean.  I give it 1 ☆

Service: The staff were friendly and helpful.  I give it 1 ☆

Decor: I loved the decor it had nice sitting areas, so it looked like it was a cool spot to hang out in or meet up with friends or even a small group.
The ambiance depends on what customers are there. If you have customers that are going to bring their noisy and rowdy, kids that are going to be running around, then you may not want to stay there and hang out and read a book or work on your computer or bring friends there. So it really depends if you're lucky or not.

Food: I bought a Portuguese egg tart, which was crispy,  buttery, and sweet. The custard was creamy and not too sweet.  The chocolate cream hornet was delicious, the chocolate flavor was on point, and the outside was sugary but not as crispy as I expected. I bought a coffee cake, custard bun and another pastries I haven't tried. I also got a tiramisu latte 😋
So far, what I've tried was delicious.
I give it 1☆

Prices: The bill was $23. Prices were expensive, I give it 0 ☆

Final Score: 4 ☆☆☆☆

I would recommend  this restaurant to others.

reviews_data.review_text: It was loud, dirty and the pastries were just ok. The staff seemed distracted. They didn't key in a drink and I had to literally flag down the barista (who was 2 ft away) for honey.

Upon entering, the first thing I noticed was the condition of the glass in the upper seating area, which was marked with fingerprints and smudges—giving an overall impression of poor maintenance. The establishment appeared unkempt, which is disappointing given the type of experience it aims to provide.

While I didn’t specifically request it, I was surprised that warming the pastry wasn’t offered—especially after the staff declined my request to have the to-go pastries cut in half.

The coffee itself was underwhelming: it was lukewarm, overfilled to the point of spillage, and lacked the quality one would expect at this price point.

Overall, the experience did not meet expectations. For the premium pricing, I had anticipated a higher level of service, cleanliness, and attention to detail. The establishment has potential, but it currently falls short of delivering a memorable or satisfying visit.
Picked up a loaf of sourdough bread, and it was the perfect mix of chewy and crispy.

I normally go to Tous in pineville or south end and I don’t have issues however for whatever reason it’s always an underwhelming Experience for this location when it comes to the staff being irritable and my drink always comes out tasting watered down, and nasty. This is the last straw wont be coming back to this location again.
Wonderful atmosphere and excellent selection.  The staff is very friendly and helpful.

Tous Les Jours is always a treat! This time I tried the matcha tea cheesecake and an iced tea- both were delicious. The vibe here is out of this world-cozy, lively, and perfect for catching up with friends or just chilling solo. Always love stopping by whenever I'm in the area. Highly recommend!

I have visited this place a few times and have always enjoyed all the baked goods we have tried. Cakes are pricey but worth it!! Fluffy, and not super sweet.
Their customer service is not the best. Last time we were there, the girl behind the counter saw many people waiting to order a cake and only stared at them… we had to tell them to go to the register to order.
La panadería y repostería está excelente en este lugar, una gran variedad de dulces ha sido un excelente lugar para tomar un buen café y disfrutar un postre
Went for Mother's Day and it was busy so this may account for the score.
Great pastries
I liked this bakery. We stopped by to get some coffee and croissants. I had the strawberry cream croissant and an iced tiramisu latte. I would recommend both. I will definitely go back again.
Delicious coffee and pastries.
When its in your beard you know it's good. 😂

reviews_data.review_text: Great place. Everything was delicious. We will be back and try more stuff

What a lovely bakery! My family and I visited when we were looking for something sweet that was in close proximity to our hotel. We got a caramel apple pie, slice of cloud cake, strawberry cream cake and a strawberry croissant. Everything was delicious and baked to perfection. I usually avoid sweet desserts and pastries because of the intense amount of sugar but these had the right amount of sweetness for me. I can see why the strawberry croissant was labeled as one of the staff's favorite. The staff was friendly and helpful.

reviews_data.review_text: I went here yesterday for the first time and had the BEST experience, the food was amazing, i got the caramel macchiato per the recommendation from the girl at the counter with the glasses with the big smile and she has the best attitude you can really see how much she loves her job i will absolutely be returning on my work breaks for more and hopefully shes there!! great job everyone!!

French-Asian Bakery Heaven! 🥐✨

Okay wow — this place totally blew us away. It’s like a dream combo of French and Asian flavors, and we wanted to try everything on the menu.

📍 The Place:
Super cute and clean, very aesthetic with all the white tones. There’s a cozy spot by the windows that’s perfect if you’re flying solo with a coffee, plus a second floor if it gets busy.
Pro tip: maybe avoid sitting in a spot near the microwave — not the best seat in the house.

🍰 The Goods:
We tried like 7 different things because... why not?

Blueberry Cloud Cake: SO good. Light, fresh, fluffy, not too sweet, and honestly just gorgeous to look at.

Pink Bread (not the real name, but you’ll know it when you see it): I loved this one — the filling was super soft and just hit the spot.

Also tried:

Mango Donut: filled with mango cream — yum.

Sweet Frank Roll: a fun little bun with sausage inside — Good!

Croque Monsieur: cheesy, warm, and super satisfying. That cheese sauce was chef’s kiss.

Blueberry Cream Cheese Bread: decent, but probably my least favorite of the bunch.

👀 The Service:
Really friendly and quick! We got our order fast, and everyone was super nice.

🚗 Parking: there is not parking lot, so you’ll need to find street parking or a nearby lot.

Would totally go back.
They run out of baked goods by mid afternoon. However their savory and sweet baked items I had were good

I’ve always enjoyed the food at this bakery, it’s consistently good, and the small patio is a nice place to sit. However, I had a very disappointing and concerning experience that I feel needs to be shared.

While sitting on the patio, my husband sat on a chair that turned out to be broken, and he fell. Thankfully, he wasn’t seriously injured, but the situation could have been much worse, especially for an elderly person. I went inside right away and informed the young woman at the register. I told her that I had moved the broken chair to the corner to prevent anyone else from getting hurt and asked her to remove it. She didn’t acknowledge me properly, didn’t seem concerned at all, and just gave a cold, dismissive response.

We walked around the area and returned about 15–20 minutes later, and the broken chair was still sitting there, completely unattended. No one had come out to remove it.

At that point, I called the store and asked to speak with a manager, and the same girl answered the phone. She told me flatly, “We don’t have a manager.” Again, no concern, no accountability.

This experience left me really disappointed. The food may be good, but the lack of basic customer service and care for customer safety is unacceptable. I sincerely hope the management (if there is any) takes this seriously and makes improvements, because it’s only a matter of time before someone really gets hurt.
the ube matcha latte (lightly sweet) with coconut milk is amazing

This is a French Asian bakery, it’s very cute inside! When you walk in you grab a tray & tongs & take what pastry items you want. If you’re eating there, they have a microwave you can use. The pastries are fresh & very flavorful! There are so many options, I wanted to try them all! I also ordered the ube latte & it was delicious!!
Tasty and quality food. Only reason for 4 star rating is We went in the evening and the options are few ( All sold out - good for them ) :-)

This is a beautiful bakery and a very relaxing place to sit and talk. So many options it was hard to choose, but we went with the spinach feta Danish, and egg custard, and the fruit Danish. Along with a hot Americano and iced honey lavender macchiato.
350F for 7 minutes to revive your croissant !
The desserts in this place are insanely good as well as the drinks
I sometimes drive from Columbia, SC just to go here and go home. I've never had anything that wasn't delicious. My only complaint is that I don't live closer.

reviews_data.review_text: Great price. Tasty bake goods, fresh and not overly sweet. Great place to get together with a friend or a date. My son picked a cake for his birthday and it was really good plus great price.
It’s one of my favorite places to study/ grab a coffee or my fav combo is the Korean garlic bomb with the one late iced definitely would recommend

Today I bought 2 almond croissants and a couple of other items.  Firstly, the other items I purchased were just fine.  They needed to be heated up anyway so I have no complaints.  But can I tell you that the almond croissants tasted very much about 2 days old!!!  I’ve had day-old bread that was much fresher.  These things were NOT fresh and I am super unhappy about it.  This place is super cute, with great customer service…but the dry hard pastry should not be a thing.  Especially at the price point these items are being sold at.   So please do not respond by saying the pastry was fresh…because if these were fresh then there is an even bigger issue at hand, because they were dry and hard.  Like all the buttery moisture had just dissipated.  Even the almond filling was dry and brittle. Just utterly choke-worthy.  Let’s do better yall!  And just to see if you guys do better, I will return and purchase the same items.  Just giving you guys a heads up because I want to sing your praises…but I will absolutely tell the truth.
Very busy place, line a bit long but service is efficient as possible.

This is one of my favorite places to go for coffee and a meal or snack. This Tous les Jours in particular has a great atmosphere. Everything that I have ever tried from here has been excellent. I have brought several of my friends and family members here and everyone has loved it.

reviews_data.review_text: The honey lavender macchiato is absolutely delicious!
The best one by far.

During my last two visits, the customer service was terrible. It wasn’t overly crowded, yet I felt like I was inconveniencing them just by wanting to pay for my pastries. Also, the sliding glass doors were wide open, which isn’t great for food safety.
Phenomenal pastry and lovely atmosphere
Fantastic venue with good coffee
The best cafe in this area !!!! Girl who is working here Dasha from Ukraine is so friendly and kind. Thanks  again for such a sweet attitude
Nice place and polite staff. I would especially like to mention the girl at the checkout, Dasha - friendly, always smiling and uplifting.

Convenient: Ample free parking in same building’s garage  when we arrived at 2:30 on a Saturday.

Food: Lived up to hype. Smoothest latte I’ve ever had. Could taste coffee without bitterness. Carmel almond pastry was divine, without being filling. Caramel apple pie pastry was what you’d imagine - the flakiness of a pastry with the flavor of the pie. I liked that the shell was flaky,  but not so flaky that it crumbled all over my  clothes. I definitely will investigate one of their “cloud cakes” on my next visit. I’m a tightwad and I’d have no trouble buying one of those cakes, which start at $38.

Ambience:  light and clean  with an interesting interpretation of stadium seating.

Service:  speedy if not particularly friendly. Place was busy whole time we were there, but line at register never got more than three deep even when line at pastry bar was eight deep.

Work environment: a tad loud. Did not try Wi-fi, but folks were working on laptops downstairs.  I did not see any plugs.  Will definitely be back, even if it’s just for a coffee.
My favorite is the earl grey macaron, cappucino with oat milk, and the cloud cake with strawberries.
So happy to see my favorite Korean bakery in CLT! I especially recommend their cakes and drinks.

I sent them an email a few weeks ago letting them know that the sliding class door on the pastry cabinet needs to be replaced. There is only one sliding door, leaving the pasties completely exposed and susceptible to gnats which I saw on the pastries when I was there. People leave their tongs inside the cabinets which is unsanitary and the employees do absolutely nothing to maintain its upkeep. I haven’t gotten a return email and the problems still remain. I will not be returning until this is resolved.

Watch your stuff and count your change. Five visits in a row and it is never right.

They either don't pack all my items, give me the wrong and cheaper cake, give me incorrect change back, or the wrong coffee order.

By now, I must believe it is on purpose. Go somewhere else if you want honest service.

One girl was nice. The other two are just grumpy every time.

The pastries and other bakery items at this establishment are deserving of a five-star rating; they're simply delicious. However, the overall atmosphere leaves something to be desired. It's odd that while they don’t warm your pastries in an oven, there is a microwave available in the dining area for you to use. The cleanliness could use some improvement as the overall area was a bit dirty. The staff appeared somewhat confused as well, though I'm not sure why. Despite these issues, I plan to return, but it's clear that there are areas in need of improvement.

A very cute place. The seating is very different and interesting. There is a minimum guarantee for almost all the items. The croissants were amazing. Blueberry cloud cake was good. The yuzu puff pastry was not the best. Tried Tiramisu latte. Didn’t have anything tiramisu about it. A good hangout place.
Pretty crowded. The restrooms are maintained well.

I found out about this bakery on my visit back home in MN. I was so impressed I had to find a location near me here in Charlotte so I was very happy to learn Charlotte has a few locations. I live near this one so I came and checked it out on Christmas day with my sons. This was their first visit. Overall it was a very nice Christmas day treat. We all enjoyed our pastries that seem to have just the right about of sweetness in them and that's what I love most about this bakery, you don't feel guilty about indulging in a sweet treat because it's not overly sugary. They have other goodies as well that aren't sweet so if desserts aren't your thing you can still find something for you. The only thing that I don't like is they don't heat up your pastries but they do have a microwave you can use in the dining area and also my latte wasn't hot enough for me. It was like as soon as I picked it up from the counter it was already warm which is weird as I had literally picked it up as soon as she finished making it so idk if they're machine was faulty or they just don't use the hottest setting or what but when I order coffee I like it hot, I do not like cold or room temp coffee at all lol and I understand not serving it extremely hot but I should feel some kind of heat when I'm drinking it lol.

I brought my family from Argentina here because this is my favorite bakery in the city. The seating, pastries, service, drinks, EVERYTHING is superb here. Even at 7 PM we were served the most delicious and fresh baked goods.

The pastries are amazing. However, the service I received was not good at all. There was no greeting when we entered. We received a very unpleasant response when asked a question. I will out return to this location for this reason.

Visited the location this morning for pastry and a latte.  The pastries are always delicious. Unfortunate, the customer service of the associates/employees at the register and coffee bar could better.  The employees demeanor need to be improvement with coaching from the owner how to interact with the customers. Also the microwave was not working, no signage was in place to let the customer know it was not working.
The cakes are so light and delicious. Wow!!! 😋
Friendly helpful service, lots of options including classics and nouveau desserts.
Good coffee and food.
Love both locations! The strawberry cloud cake is so delicious and so is the melon bread!

The pastries are delicious here, and the bakery boasts spacious seating areas, making it a perfect spot to relax while enjoying a treat. Whether you're in the mood for something sweet or savory, there's plenty to choose from!

I went here about a year ago and recently drove past and recalled how wonderful the food and drinks were. A new favorite.
Everything in the cases looked so good, had a cheese and blueberry danish and a mango donut.
We ordered about seven items and every one of them were fresh and delicious. I can’t wait to go back!
Solid

Great spot for a quick breakfast bite. The service was quick and the food was tasty. The music was very loud, which made it difficult to hear the servers. But otherwise, a great spot for a quick breakfast.

I come here often and just hang out — sometimes for hours on in while reading my Bible, a book or journaling. I really love the atmosphere and ease of access with parking! I’ve tried both dessert items and actual food items like the frank rolls and everything is always very tasty. My fave, go-to beverage that they introduced me to is the Honey Lavender Macchiato 😋 always made promptly and to my liking. Anytime there’s an issue, it’s resolved just as promptly and to my liking. A while back, I came in one day and hip hop music was blasting over the speakers and it really interrupted my experience and lowered the atmosphere. I reached out to let management know and to also offer more on-brand suggestions and I’m really happy to have seen them ensure that it never happens again. Today, they have some beautiful soft jazz playing at a good volume level & it’s been a great visit 🥰
Some stuff is good some stuff is out for a while so it doesn't take taste fresh.
Nice place and good food
The Best !

Today, we visited this bakery for the first time, and I must say, I was completely won over by the cleanliness, variety of baked goods, and the cozy atmosphere. On top of that, we absolutely loved the flavors of everything we tried! The Spinach Feta Danish, Sweet Cheese and Blueberry Danish, and the Strawberry Pastry were especially delicious. The sweetness was perfectly balanced, which we appreciated since we’re not fans of overly sugary pastries. The only downside was the lack of high chairs for babies. However, our little one absolutely loved the milk bread, so that made up for it! We’re already looking forward to visiting again and trying more of their treats.
A work of art! We buy the birthday cake from here every year. Top bakery in Charlotte!
Wonderful Asian bakery with lots of sweet treats to enjoy. I highly recommend trying the milk cream bread and the Iced honey lemon tea with Earl Grey.
Expensive but the cakes are way better than a cake you could get a grocery store.  My wife is Korean and she loved the cake I bought here for her birthday, very authentic.

reviews_data.review_text: Great French inspired bakeries. I will always get my cakes from here. Ome of the servers, Ann, was also very friendly and made great drinks!

Such a chill place.  Grab a tray, fill it up with goodies, order coffee, check out then choose a seat in the sun.  Everything was delicious, but if you love honey, get the honey bread/toast. Thank me later.

**Bakery Review: Tous Les Jours - Southpark**

Tous Les Jours in Southpark is an absolute gem of a bakery, located conveniently near Bentley's Restaurant and attached to a parking deck. The beautiful entrance and modern, well-lit interior set the stage for an extraordinary experience the moment you walk in.

As you step inside, you’re immediately greeted by a dazzling display of baked goods in well-lit cases. The sight is nothing short of mesmerizing, showcasing the bakery's incredible pastries and bread designs. It’s clear that a significant amount of care and time goes into creating each intricate piece. The carving into the breads before baking results in exquisite designs that are truly a feast for the eyes once baked.

The attention to detail and craftsmanship in every item is evident, making it impossible not to admire the artistry on display. The baked goods are not only visually stunning but also mouth-wateringly delicious.

My wife and I were fascinated by our visit and were pleasantly surprised to discover such a high-quality bakery in Southpark. This bakery is now a must-visit for us whenever we are in the area for dinner. We can't wait to return for more delightful desserts.

Thank you so much to the Tous Les Jours team for an unforgettable experience. We look forward to many more visits!

This is the first time we came across a slice of a moldy cake at this bakery (See the pic where it turned grey. It's supposed to be a light purple color). We frequently visit both Pineville and South Park locations. And yesterday I bought 2 slices of cake and one came moldy. They should be very careful about taking these bad items off the shelves.

I called the store and they offered a replacement but kids were so disappointed, don't want to go back to this location. We still love Tous les Jours, but will be very careful next time.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello!! Raj
We’re so sorry you had a negative experience at our store, and we thank you for your previous patronage. We make our cakes every day and only then set them for sale. Sometimes, discoloration happens for a variety of reasons, but please rest assured that it is not mold. However, we understand that seeing it is nonetheless distressing, and we’re very sorry this happened to you and your family. If you have any further comments, please let us know.Also, Please ask for a manager next time you stop by because we would love the opportunity to serve you again!! Thank you.

reviews_data.review_text: If you are a pastry and bakery lover this place is for you, big assortment  of sweets and treats, and beverages. One star down for my matcha tea that was barely warm when i got it, i didn’t complain bc they were super busy with holiday crowd. Hope next visit will be better.

We bought a cake on December 30th for New Years but they only have few Holiday cake selections unlike on December 24th maybe because it’s not New Years eve yet. We decided to just buy the Strawberry Cloud Cake and then we asked the lady who assisted us if we can ask for the “Happy Holiday” topper and she replied right away “I dont think so”. Then she went to the lady who was preparing the cake on the corner and came back said “No, only for the Holiday cakes”. The lady in the corner turned around and look at us bluntly and went back in preparing the cake. We were shocked for a $46 cake and for just a small topper they will treat us that way. To think on Thanksgiving Eve, we bought Ube Cloud Cake and they gave us the “Give Thanks” topper when we asked for it. And we always buy almost $200 everytime we go there since we are 30mins away from this place.  We like their cakes and pastries so we buy a lot everytime we are there. But, this time it seems that they are not in the mood to serve their customers. We are attaching photos of cakes that we bought these recent holidays, so that you’ll see that their customer service are not consistent. Anyhow, we are not coming back!

reviews_data.review_text: Wanted to try something new for our family outing so we decided to come here for some patties and coffee. The customer service was  -3/10, the pastries was 5/10 & the coffee was -1/10 considering I asked for iced coffee but they gave me hot in 80 degree weather! Probably won't be back.

Dear Tous Le Jour,
I've been a loyal fan of this coffee shop since moving here. it's truly one of my favorite spots in town. The coffee and pastries are consistently great, the atmosphere is cozy, and the staff are always kind and welcoming.

My friends and I haven’t been going since reading about the low scores and violations in the health inspections. As someone who genuinely loves and supports this place, I hope the team is able to address the issues raised and take the necessary steps to bring everything up to standard.

I'm rooting for you and looking forward to many more great cups of coffee here in the future!

Used to be my go to place.  No more.  Horrific sanitation scores - repeatedly. Either they don’t care or they care incapable of maintaining a safe sanitation level. Not a problem with their other location but I’m really turned off.

That young brunette woman needs to get fired. I’ve had a couple occasions with her being passive aggressive and downright rude, making me feel like I was inconveniencing her by simply placing my order. Her customer service is unacceptable.

I also saw her involved in a verbal altercation with another customer/family outside a couple of months ago. If she cannot conduct herself respectfully and professionally, she should not be in a customer service role.

Everything is 100% perfect!! Food is always fresh and the bakery, usually flaky and fluffy!
I tried most of their bakery and ordered 2 cakes and they were absolutely delicious and not over sugary, just balanced and creamy!

reviews_data.review_text: Unfortunately the owners are disassociated with the standards of cleanliness. They have low marks from the health board, for multiple years. They're neglected to train their employees, give process to the employees about how to keep clean, and store food. They do not spend money on protecting the kitchen from roaches, and in part this is also the responsibility of the overall building management. Yet that only means the retail tenants need to be more aggressive with bug product on the ground where the food should never be... so it is only a matter of time before they change ownership or close. There are other quality French cafes with baked goods in the area.

There’s a lady who’s almost always there and usually makes the drinks. One time, she even took my order. She always looks annoyed, acts like she doesn’t hear you, and just stares blankly when you talk. This has happened many times, and at this point, I really hope she’s not there the next time I go in.

Love this place and it is considered one of my favorites.  I will make it a point to drive there at least once a month since I am 21/2 hours away. Sadly, Tous les Jours doesn't want to make a satellite home here in Chapin SC.  They would definitely knock the socks off any place here.

Thank you, Susan Adams

I'm addicted!  These pastries are some of the best.  Nothing is too sweet.  They add fresh fruit in some desserts.  The cloud cakes are perfect.  The cream you see in pictures is a light cream not icing.  Everything is reasonably priced.  And their dough is so light and fluffy in everything I've eaten from there.

I’ll start off with the coffee is amazing! I ordered the 20oz iced caramel macchiato. I love matcha and they had a few different matcha options that I’d love to try in the future. I also ordered the spinach & cheese danish. They serve it warm and it tastes very good but it’s kind of small in comparison to other spinach danishes that I’ve had, and it costs more.

I also ordered a lemon macaron. Pretty large for a macaron! I love the texture but it was too tart. Not a huge fan of the flavor but I’m sure the other macarons are good. And they have a large variety to include pistachio, red velvet, and earl grey.

Parking is very difficult. I drove around multiple times and to even park in their lot is hard because it is so tiny. And I paid $17 for a coffee, danish, and macaron which really should’ve been a few dollars less.
I love it so much. Food was amazing 10/10 experience.

The place is pretty, so are the pastries- (that’s just about all some of them have (looks)), but there are like four good items. The service took a little while but patience is the greatest of all virtues, I guess. I know the workers were trying their best but they 1) seemed uninterested, 2) the coffee tasted like tea- steamed pretty lazily. I NEVER leave reviews, but this was straight up bad and sad. I was so excited to try Tous Les Jours.

The cloud cakes have nothing cloudy about them. Theyre also too expensive for what they are! They’re tough and the flavors a feel nonexistent. They taste like vanilla cakes with food coloring. The icing felt old, it was super greasy. As if the icing had begun to separate between the sugar and butter- or worse; it wasn’t mixed well. $7 for that. The macarons also had little to no flavor apart from sugar. They tasted like fridge. I was a little sad to taste everything, knowing the packaging says “freshly baked everyday”. Nothing about it tasted freshly baked. The mocha just tasted like packaged hot chocolate mix. No strong hints of anything else (coffee). Made my tummy hurt. I don’t mean to sound entitled but I led a bakery program last summer for kids and I can tell you, I know when cakes are old. Everything was sort of tough. The chocolate on stuff also felt very pasty and chalky. The chocolate was waxy, and seemed low quality. Some stuff is good but please don’t try this with high expectations. Not worth a visit imo. Sorry :(

Visiting from out of town morning of 6/6/25- searched for a quaint coffee/pastry shop and chose Tous Les Jours.  Food was well presented and atmosphere just ok - but the Barista was very unfriendly and disinterested and basically seemed annoyed by the customers.  With so many shops like this in the Charlotte area - I’ll search for one with friendlier employees.

reviews_data.review_text: It was loud, dirty and the pastries were just ok. The staff seemed distracted. They didn't key in a drink and I had to literally flag down the barista (who was 2 ft away) for honey.

Upon entering, the first thing I noticed was the condition of the glass in the upper seating area, which was marked with fingerprints and smudges—giving an overall impression of poor maintenance. The establishment appeared unkempt, which is disappointing given the type of experience it aims to provide.

While I didn’t specifically request it, I was surprised that warming the pastry wasn’t offered—especially after the staff declined my request to have the to-go pastries cut in half.

The coffee itself was underwhelming: it was lukewarm, overfilled to the point of spillage, and lacked the quality one would expect at this price point.

Overall, the experience did not meet expectations. For the premium pricing, I had anticipated a higher level of service, cleanliness, and attention to detail. The establishment has potential, but it currently falls short of delivering a memorable or satisfying visit.

reviews_data.review_text: I went here yesterday for the first time and had the BEST experience, the food was amazing, i got the caramel macchiato per the recommendation from the girl at the counter with the glasses with the big smile and she has the best attitude you can really see how much she loves her job i will absolutely be returning on my work breaks for more and hopefully shes there!! great job everyone!!

French-Asian Bakery Heaven! 🥐✨

Okay wow — this place totally blew us away. It’s like a dream combo of French and Asian flavors, and we wanted to try everything on the menu.

📍 The Place:
Super cute and clean, very aesthetic with all the white tones. There’s a cozy spot by the windows that’s perfect if you’re flying solo with a coffee, plus a second floor if it gets busy.
Pro tip: maybe avoid sitting in a spot near the microwave — not the best seat in the house.

🍰 The Goods:
We tried like 7 different things because... why not?

Blueberry Cloud Cake: SO good. Light, fresh, fluffy, not too sweet, and honestly just gorgeous to look at.

Pink Bread (not the real name, but you’ll know it when you see it): I loved this one — the filling was super soft and just hit the spot.

Also tried:

Mango Donut: filled with mango cream — yum.

Sweet Frank Roll: a fun little bun with sausage inside — Good!

Croque Monsieur: cheesy, warm, and super satisfying. That cheese sauce was chef’s kiss.

Blueberry Cream Cheese Bread: decent, but probably my least favorite of the bunch.

👀 The Service:
Really friendly and quick! We got our order fast, and everyone was super nice.

🚗 Parking: there is not parking lot, so you’ll need to find street parking or a nearby lot.

Would totally go back.
They run out of baked goods by mid afternoon. However their savory and sweet baked items I had were good

I’ve always enjoyed the food at this bakery, it’s consistently good, and the small patio is a nice place to sit. However, I had a very disappointing and concerning experience that I feel needs to be shared.

While sitting on the patio, my husband sat on a chair that turned out to be broken, and he fell. Thankfully, he wasn’t seriously injured, but the situation could have been much worse, especially for an elderly person. I went inside right away and informed the young woman at the register. I told her that I had moved the broken chair to the corner to prevent anyone else from getting hurt and asked her to remove it. She didn’t acknowledge me properly, didn’t seem concerned at all, and just gave a cold, dismissive response.

We walked around the area and returned about 15–20 minutes later, and the broken chair was still sitting there, completely unattended. No one had come out to remove it.

At that point, I called the store and asked to speak with a manager, and the same girl answered the phone. She told me flatly, “We don’t have a manager.” Again, no concern, no accountability.

This experience left me really disappointed. The food may be good, but the lack of basic customer service and care for customer safety is unacceptable. I sincerely hope the management (if there is any) takes this seriously and makes improvements, because it’s only a matter of time before someone really gets hurt.

reviews_data.review_text: Great price. Tasty bake goods, fresh and not overly sweet. Great place to get together with a friend or a date. My son picked a cake for his birthday and it was really good plus great price.
It’s one of my favorite places to study/ grab a coffee or my fav combo is the Korean garlic bomb with the one late iced definitely would recommend

Today I bought 2 almond croissants and a couple of other items.  Firstly, the other items I purchased were just fine.  They needed to be heated up anyway so I have no complaints.  But can I tell you that the almond croissants tasted very much about 2 days old!!!  I’ve had day-old bread that was much fresher.  These things were NOT fresh and I am super unhappy about it.  This place is super cute, with great customer service…but the dry hard pastry should not be a thing.  Especially at the price point these items are being sold at.   So please do not respond by saying the pastry was fresh…because if these were fresh then there is an even bigger issue at hand, because they were dry and hard.  Like all the buttery moisture had just dissipated.  Even the almond filling was dry and brittle. Just utterly choke-worthy.  Let’s do better yall!  And just to see if you guys do better, I will return and purchase the same items.  Just giving you guys a heads up because I want to sing your praises…but I will absolutely tell the truth.

I definitely will investigate one of their “cloud cakes” on my next visit. I’m a tightwad and I’d have no trouble buying one of those cakes, which start at $38.

Ambience:  light and clean  with an interesting interpretation of stadium seating.

Service:  speedy if not particularly friendly. Place was busy whole time we were there, but line at register never got more than three deep even when line at pastry bar was eight deep.

Work environment: a tad loud. Did not try Wi-fi, but folks were working on laptops downstairs.  I did not see any plugs.  Will definitely be back, even if it’s just for a coffee.

I sent them an email a few weeks ago letting them know that the sliding class door on the pastry cabinet needs to be replaced. There is only one sliding door, leaving the pasties completely exposed and susceptible to gnats which I saw on the pastries when I was there. People leave their tongs inside the cabinets which is unsanitary and the employees do absolutely nothing to maintain its upkeep. I haven’t gotten a return email and the problems still remain. I will not be returning until this is resolved.

I live near this one so I came and checked it out on Christmas day with my sons. This was their first visit. Overall it was a very nice Christmas day treat. We all enjoyed our pastries that seem to have just the right about of sweetness in them and that's what I love most about this bakery, you don't feel guilty about indulging in a sweet treat because it's not overly sugary. **Bakery Review: Tous Les Jours - Southpark**

Tous Les Jours in Southpark is an absolute gem of a bakery, located conveniently near Bentley's Restaurant and attached to a parking deck. The beautiful entrance and modern, well-lit interior set the stage for an extraordinary experience the moment you walk in.

As you step inside, you’re immediately greeted by a dazzling display of baked goods in well-lit cases. The sight is nothing short of mesmerizing, showcasing the bakery's incredible pastries and bread designs. It’s clear that a significant amount of care and time goes into creating each intricate piece. The carving into the breads before baking results in exquisite designs that are truly a feast for the eyes once baked.

The attention to detail and craftsmanship in every item is evident, making it impossible not to admire the artistry on display. The baked goods are not only visually stunning but also mouth-wateringly delicious.

My wife and I were fascinated by our visit and were pleasantly surprised to discover such a high-quality bakery in Southpark. This bakery is now a must-visit for us whenever we are in the area for dinner. We can't wait to return for more delightful desserts.

Thank you so much to the Tous Les Jours team for an unforgettable experience. We look forward to many more visits!

One time I went (this was a while ago), I asked about it again, and the barista who served me on that day told me that they honestly took it off the menu because it takes a lot of effort/ time to make. I told him that it was a bummer for me cause I can’t have caffeine and that drink itself was the reason I started going to TLJ regularly in the first place. He said that he knew how to make it and offered to make it for me (it was slow at the time) which was super considerate. I told him not to worry about it because (I didn’t want to be annoying) but I genuinely respect taking something off the menu for a reason like that.

All of the baristas and staff are super sweet and accommodating. I’ve tried all their caffeine free drinks and unfortunately none of them are to my personal taste, but they have always offered to change it or refund me. I appreciate the gesture, but I think part of going out to try new things comes with the risk that you might not like what you ordered.

Tous les Jours which means “every day” in French is a South Korean bakery franchise. This place is one of the finest bakeries with fantastic ambience. Coming to pastry section, We have ordered Guava Danish, Strawberry Croissant and Chocolate croissant. Guava Danish was the winner. Green tea cloud cake and choco cloud cake were light, mouth watering and goes very well with latte. Raisin bread was fluffy, aromatic and has the right amount of sweetness. Caramel cheesecake was little bit over sweet. Coming to coffee, Iced tiramisu latte, vanilla latte, lavender latte and cappuccino were outstanding.

reviews_data.review_text:
Health hazard!
This is the first time we came across a slice of a moldy cake at this bakery (See the pic where it turned grey. It's supposed to be a light purple color). We frequently visit both Pineville and South Park locations. And yesterday I bought 2 slices of cake and one came moldy. They should be very careful about taking these bad items off the shelves.

I called the store and they offered a replacement but kids were so disappointed, don't want to go back to this location. We still love Tous les Jours, but will be very careful next time.

Hello!! Raj
We’re so sorry you had a negative experience at our store, and we thank you for your previous patronage. We make our cakes every day and only then set them for sale.
